{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Agentic Team",
  "description": "Kick off the v2 agentic development workflow. Reads a spec or Jira ticket and orchestrates builder, validator, reviewer, and documenter.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are about to kick off the agentic development workflow (v2).\n\n1. Ask the user what to work on. Accept any of:\n   - A Jira ticket key (e.g. PROJ-1234)\n   - A spec path (e.g. .kiro/specs/feature-name/)\n   - A plain description of the task\n\n2. Based on input:\n   - If Jira ticket: fetch it with the Atlassian MCP tools, summarize it, and confirm scope with the user.\n   - If spec path: read tasks.md from that spec directory and summarize the tasks.\n   - If plain description: ask the user if they want to create a spec first or go straight to execution.\n\n3. Confirm the user is on the correct feature branch (remind them the workflow assumes a branch already exists per branching-convention.md).\n\n4. Once scope is confirmed, tell the user to swap to team-lead:\n   `/agent swap` → select `team-lead`\n\n   Then provide the exact prompt to paste for team-lead, e.g.:\n   \"Execute the spec in .kiro/specs/<name>/\" or \"Implement PROJ-XXXX: <summary>\"\n\n5. If the user is already on team-lead agent, skip step 4 and begin orchestration directly."
  },
  "workspaceFolderName": "your-workspace",
  "shortName": "agentic-team"
}
